FT  22 AUG 92 / UK Company News: Dart in cash acquisition
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Dart Group has acquired Bourne Aviation Supply, a specialist in the source
and supply of modern aircraft parts and engine parts - particularly for the
Airbus and Boeing ranges.
Total maximum consideration will be Pounds 950,000 cash with a further
Pounds 850,000 payable dependent on profits over the next three years.
To achieve maximum earn-out Bourne must return aggregate pre-tax profits of
Pounds 1.32m prior to July 31 1995. For the 12 months to end-March 1992
Bourne achieved pre-tax profits of Pounds 65,000. Net assets at the year-end
amounted to Pounds 86,000.
