FT  22 AUG 92 / UK Company News: Sale Tilney agreement
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sale Tilney, which has food, industrial and financial services interests,
has reached agreement with its Isle of Man-based insurance underwriting
subsidiary, Monument Marine &amp; General, on proposals for two schemes of
arrangement involving Monument and its creditors, and Sale Tilney and
certain Monument policyholders.
If the schemes become effective Sale Tilney's beneficial interest in
Monument will be transferred to a trustee for the benefit of scheme
creditors and any further group liability in respect of Monument's losses
will be eliminated.
