<HEADLINE>
FT  22 AUG 92 / UK Company News: Northamber loss deepens to Pounds 2.75m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NORTHAMBER, the specialist computer and electronic transmission products
supplier, announced increased pre-tax losses of Pounds 2.75m for the year to
April 30 compared with Pounds 1.56m.
Although turnover was just ahead to Pounds 93.1m (Pounds 90.1m) there was an
operating loss of Pounds 2.28m (Pounds 1.07m). Mr David Phillips, the
chairman, said the loss was after taking the stock and debtor provisions
necessitated by the oversupplied and difficult market conditions.
He said the group had again ended the year debt-free, with Pounds 1.3m net
cash.
Losses per share worked through at 11.6p (7.6p) and 'with the pervading
uncertainty and in order to conserve cash' the single final dividend is cut
from 2.5p to 0.5p.
