<HEADLINE>
FT  21 AUG 92 / UK Company News: Wyevale grows to Pounds 3.1m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
WYEVALE Garden Centres yesterday reported a 40 per cent increase in pre-tax
profits, from Pounds 2.2m to Pounds 3.09m, in the six months to June 30.
Turnover of this USM-quoted group, helped by the integration of the
Cramphorn garden centres, increased by Pounds 8.68m to Pounds 20.3m.
Like-for-like sales from the Wyevale centres, taking out the effect of the
Cramphorn acquisition, showed a 3.1 per cent improvement. Net operating
margins increased from 16.9 per cent to 17.5 per cent.
Mr Christopher Powell, chairman, said the anticipated post-election upturn
had failed to materialise in a sustained manner, and trading conditions
remained extremely tough.
As a result of the Cramphorn acquisition, current levels of debt were higher
than previously experienced. However, the group remained in a strong
financial position, with gearing of 40 per cent at the period end, he added.
Basic earnings per share were unchanged at 7.3p. Fully diluted earnings
increased slightly from 6.8p to 7p. The interim dividend is maintained at
2.48p.
