<BYLINE>
   By TIM COONE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DUBLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Independent Newspapers, the Irish publishing group headed by Mr Tony
O'Reilly, announced a 35 per cent increase in pre-tax profits from IPounds
5.2m to IPounds 7m (Pounds 6.6m) for the half year to June 30.
Turnover rose by 4 per cent to IPounds 77.4m (IPounds 74.5m).
Mr O'Reilly said the result reflected improved margins in the Irish
publishing operations which had come from circulation increases, advertising
market share improvements, and introduction of new technology.
He said the group had also recently acquired a 2 per cent stake in the
Mirror Group.
Earnings per share rose by 29 per cent to 16.2p (12.6p) and an interim
dividend of 5.5p (5p) is declared.
