<HEADLINE>
FT  21 AUG 92 / Technology (Worth Watching): Body drier shoots the breeze
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LOUISE KEHOE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
An inventive, if somewhat bizarre, product from Primacare Marketing of
Bolton falls into the category of technology 'worth trying' rather than
watching.
The Cozydry electric 'body drier' is a unit that can be installed in the
corner of a shower stall. It consists of a floor to ceiling strip with
several blowers, rather like hair or hand driers. After showering, the user
simply turns on the drier and basks in streams of warm air.
'Forget wet towels. Forget the effort of rubbing. Forget the twisting and
stretching to reach those awkward places,' the inventors say. 'The Cozydry
sensation is like standing naked in a gentle breeze on a summer's day.' Not
for everyone, perhaps, the Cozydry may none the less prove a valuable
appliance for the disabled or elderly. Primacare Marketing: UK, 0204 386316.
</TEXT>
