FT  20 AUG 92 / UK Company News: Victaulic holds steady at Pounds 7m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROLAND RUDD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A FAVOURABLE cash position at Victaulic offset difficult trading conditions
enabling the pipes and fittings maker to report unchanged pre-tax profits of
Pounds 6.9m for the six months to June 30.
Turnover fell from Pounds 57.4m to Pounds 51.2m, mainly reflecting reduced
demand for pipelines from British Gas which has cut capital expenditure.
This is because of uncertainties over the future structure and ownership of
British Gas's network following the referral of these matters to the
Monopolies and Mergers Commission. The uncertainty is likely to continue
into next year.
In the group's other main market - water - some companies reduced investment
on the repair and maintainance of mains, affecting sales of Viking Johnson,
which is involved in the refurbishment of mains.
Trading profit fell from Pounds 6.79m to Pounds 6.46m. However, net cash of
Pounds 10m resulted in interest received of Pounds 461,000 (Pounds 57,000).
Cost reductions, a decline in the workforce and increased margins of 12.6
per cent (11.8 per cent) also helped.
The interim dividend is 2.5p (2.35p) on earnings unchanged at 10.3p.
